pr_body:
Fix bugs of installation among various OS, add installation scripts for further use.

## Status
**READY**

## Description
Added scripts to ease up installing dependencies. 

## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
Make sure you have sudo priveleges

## Steps to Test or Reproduce
sudo bash script_name_based_on_os.py

```sh
git pull --prune
git checkout <feature-branch>
```

## Impacted Areas in Application

* Installation

**READY**

## Description
Logs bash commands run on the system on which SecureTea is being run on

## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
Set history_logger in configuration to true or use --hist

## Steps to Test or Reproduce

```sh
python3 SecureTea.py --hist
```

## Impacted Areas in Application
List general components of the application that this PR will affect:

1. securetea/lib : history_logger added
2. args : --hist added
3. core.py : To run History logger

## Notes
+ I had my master set to the previous PR. So please ignore the commits of that PR for the time being

pr_body:
## Status
**READY**

## Description
+ Tackles [issue](https://github.com/OWASP/SecureTea-Project/issues/255)
+ Added history logger to gui
+ User's choices of arguments to run SecureTea from GUI are saved and restored
+ Introduces notifications in gui component
![SampleNotif](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29600964/86742417-bc2c6280-c055-11ea-92a9-c14731cf86a8.png)

+ Introduced try-except block for geocode


## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
None specific

## Steps to Test or Reproduce
cd ServerApp && sudo python3 run.py
cd gui && ng serve

```sh
git pull --prune
git checkout <feature-branch>
```

## Impacted Areas in Application
List general components of the application that this PR will affect:

* Added history logger option to gui
* Arguments : Added arguments :-
        1. --skip_input : Skip taking input while running SecureTea App
        2. --skip_config_file : Skip taking configuration from config file available on server side
        3. Already existing --hist is made false by default 

* Routes : Added route /notifs for SecureTea app to send notifications to the Server Flask App
* Socket : A socket opened between gui and Server Flask App to notify the user regd. attacks, warnings and information from the logger module.

pr_body:
## Status
**READY**

## Description
1. Added options to use custom scanners from clamav, yara and virus_total
2. Added eligibility traces(Reinforcement Learning) in IDS to make it a semi-IPS i.e. blacklisting frequent offenders

## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
None specific

## Steps to Test or Reproduce
Outline the steps to test or reproduce the PR here.

```sh
git pull --prune
git checkout <feature-branch>
```

1. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --clamav
2. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --yara
3. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --ids

## Impacted Areas in Application
List general components of the application that this PR will affect:

* Args and Args helper :- Added following arguments :
    1. --clamav : Use clamav for AV search true or false
    2. --yara : Use yara for AV search true or false
    3. --eligibility_threshold : Intrusion Detection System (IDS) eligibility threshold
    4. --severity_factor : Intrusion Detection System (IDS) eligibility traces severity factor
* Antivirus Scanner :- Use clamav, yara or virustotal AV scanner as per args
* IDS :- Auto blacklist and whitelist IPs based on eligibility traces, a RL algorithm. It is explained in detail in [documentation](https://github.com/kUSHAL0601/SecureTea-Project/blob/eligibility-traces/doc/en-US/user_guide.md#setting-up-intrusion-detection-system) making it a semi-IPS by preventing malicious attackers.

## Status
**READY**

## Description
+ Tackles [issue](https://github.com/OWASP/SecureTea-Project/issues/255)
+ Added history logger to gui
+ User's choices of arguments to run SecureTea from GUI are saved and restored
+ Introduces notifications in gui component
![SampleNotif](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29600964/86742417-bc2c6280-c055-11ea-92a9-c14731cf86a8.png)

+ Introduced try-except block for geocode


## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
None specific

## Steps to Test or Reproduce
cd ServerApp && sudo python3 run.py
cd gui && ng serve

```sh
git pull --prune
git checkout <feature-branch>
```

## Impacted Areas in Application
List general components of the application that this PR will affect:

* Added history logger option to gui
* Arguments : Added arguments :-
        1. --skip_input : Skip taking input while running SecureTea App
        2. --skip_config_file : Skip taking configuration from config file available on server side
        3. Already existing --hist is made false by default 

* Routes : Added route /notifs for SecureTea app to send notifications to the Server Flask App
* Socket : A socket opened between gui and Server Flask App to notify the user regd. attacks, warnings and information from the logger module.

## Status
**READY**

## Description
1. Added options to use custom scanners from clamav, yara and virus_total
2. Added eligibility traces(Reinforcement Learning) in IDS to make it a semi-IPS i.e. blacklisting frequent offenders

## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
None specific

## Steps to Test or Reproduce
Outline the steps to test or reproduce the PR here.

```sh
git pull --prune
git checkout <feature-branch>
```

1. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --clamav
2. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --yara
3. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --ids

## Impacted Areas in Application
List general components of the application that this PR will affect:

* Args and Args helper :- Added following arguments :
    1. --clamav : Use clamav for AV search true or false
    2. --yara : Use yara for AV search true or false
    3. --eligibility_threshold : Intrusion Detection System (IDS) eligibility threshold
    4. --severity_factor : Intrusion Detection System (IDS) eligibility traces severity factor
* Antivirus Scanner :- Use clamav, yara or virustotal AV scanner as per args
* IDS :- Auto blacklist and whitelist IPs based on eligibility traces, a RL algorithm. It is explained in detail in [documentation](https://github.com/kUSHAL0601/SecureTea-Project/blob/eligibility-traces/doc/en-US/user_guide.md#setting-up-intrusion-detection-system) making it a semi-IPS by preventing malicious attackers.

## Status
**READY**

## Description
Introduces Social Engineering, Bug Fixes, Documentation addition and fixes

## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation

## Deploy Notes
None

## Steps to Test or Reproduce

```sh
git pull --prune
git checkout <feature-branch>
```
+ CLI
    1. sudo python3 SecureTea.py --social_eng_email="yourmailid"
    2. python3 SocialEngineering.py
+ GUI
    1. cd gui && ng serve
     2. sudo ServerApp/run.py


## Impacted Areas in Application

* GUI : Added gui support for IDS, SocialEngineering
* Arguments : Option for social engineering email id added as an arg
* SocialEngineering.py : To run Social Engineering on given mail id
* Core.py : Server support for gui added features
* Documentation : Documentation for Social Engineering added, discrepancies fixed

## Status
**READY**

## Description
Fixes [test case](https://github.com/OWASP/SecureTea-Project/blob/master/test/test_monitor.py)

## Todos
- [x] Tests
- [x] Documentation


## Deploy Notes
Make sure unittest/pytest is installed

## Steps to Test or Reproduce

```sh
git clone https://github.com/OWASP/SecureTea-Project.git
cd SecureTea-Project
python3 -m virtualenv sectest
source sectest/bin/activate
cp SecreTea.py ~
cd
pip install git+https://github.com/OWASP/SecureTea-Project.git
python3 SecureTea.py
```

```sh
git clone https://github.com/OWASP/SecureTea-Project.git
cd SecureTea-Project
python3 -m pytest test/test_monitor.py
```


## Impacted Areas in Application
* pip install
* testing
